Descriptive Statistics

Packages

library(car)
library(emmeans)
library(ggpubr)
library(lme4)
library(lmerTest)
library(mlogit)
library(report)
library(sjPlot)
library(tidyverse)
library(viridis)

Data Preparation

data <- readxl::read_excel("../data/data.xlsx", sheet = 2) %>% 
  mutate(Subject = if_else(Subject == "NP.", "NP", Subject),
         Passage = if_else(Passage == "d", "Dialogue", "Narrative"),
         Age = if_else(Age == 1, "Younger", "Older"),
         isBilingual = as.logical(if_else(isBilingual == 1, TRUE, FALSE)), 
         L1 = if_else(L1 == 1, "Polish", "German")) %>% 
  mutate_all(as.factor)
data.count <- data %>% 
  group_by(Participant, Sex, isBilingual, L1, Subject, Age, Passage) %>%
  summarise(SCount = length(Subject)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  group_by(Participant) %>%
  mutate(Participant = as.factor(Participant)) %>%
  ungroup()

Data Exploration

data %>% group_by(Subject, L1, Passage) %>%
  summarise(Count = length(Subject)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  group_by(L1, Passage) %>%
  mutate(Percentage = Count * 100 / sum(Count))

data %>% filter(Passage == "Dialogue") %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = isBilingual, fill = Subject)) + 
  geom_bar(position = "fill", width = 0.4, col = "black") + 
  facet_wrap(~L1 + Age) + 
  ylab("Proportion of Subject Types") + 
  xlab("Participant is Bilingual") +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(aspect.ratio = 1/1) + 
  scale_fill_viridis_d(option = "mako") -> dialogue

data %>% filter(Passage == "Narrative") %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = isBilingual, fill = Subject)) + 
  geom_bar(position = "fill", width = 0.4, col = "black") + 
  facet_wrap(~L1 + Age) + 
  ylab("") + 
  xlab("") +

  scale_fill_viridis_d(option = "mako") -> narrative

Modelling

Polish Data

data.count %>% filter(L1 == "Polish") %>% 
  mutate_all(as.factor) %>%
  mutate(SCount = as.numeric(SCount)) %>%
  glmer(formula = SCount ~ Subject * Passage + Subject * isBilingual + Subject * Age + (1 | Participant), 
        family = "poisson", control = glmerControl(optimizer = "bobyqa")) -> model
Anova(model, type = "III")
